You will be provided a design mockup as a PDF-file and must replicate that design in HTML and CSS. 

 responsive website that will display images, descriptions and links to each of the portfolio projects

 continue tweaking and making customizations to the design to personalize it 


notes on project requirements

design - dom tree rep page content - elements semantic tags, grid based layout

responsive - responsively designed, renders appropriately, required components 3 req devices - ipad, nexus 5 phone, laptop

separation of concerns - portfolio separates structure (HTML) from design/style (CSS)

code quality - code is formatted with consistent, logical, easy to read formatting (style guide)

exceeds - personalizes, adds functionality


   1. Download the design mockup file from the Downloadables section to your lower right hand corner and review it.

   2.  Identify the various boxes you will need to build in order to recreate this design.

    3. Write your HTML and CSS files, continue to iterate until your work is representative of the design mockup.

   4.  Take the time to personalize your portfolio with custom colors, additional content and your own images.

   5.  Validate your HTML and CSS against the W3C's Validators. Note: the validators consider the following errors, whereas Udacity accepts these errors as acceptable:

        HTML5: Bad value X-UA-Compatible for attribute http-equiv on element meta when using the X-UA-Compatible meta tag.

        CSS3: Property [some property here] is an unknown vendor extension when using vendor prefixed properties (like -moz-box-sizing).

BOOTSTRAP GRID SYSTEM:

- rows placed within a .container or .container-fluid
- use rows to create horizontal groups of columns
- content placed within columns, and only columns may be immediate children of rows

to check your rows add:

* {
    border: 1px solid red !important;
}